Oracle :	(Max no. of columns 1000 per table)
========

Datatypes : 
-----------
>	char(size)		:	max 2000 chars
>	varchar2(size)	:	max 4000 chars
>	number(Precision, scale) :	max value for precision(total length) is 38, and scale denotes digits after decimal.
>	Date			:	DD-MMM-YY	(2digits_of_date-3chars_of_month-last_2_digits_of_year)
>	raw(size)		:	max 2KB, to store logos, thumb impressions, photos etc.
>	long			:	max 2GB, to store variable length of char data (only one Column per table of type LONG)
>	long raw		:	max 2 GB, similar to "raw"  (only one Column per table of type LONG RAW)
>	lob				:	max 4GB, large Object 
								:	BLOB	(binary)
								:	CLOB	(char)
								:	NCLOB	(binary or char)

>	Allowed Chars	:	a-z, A-Z, 0-9, $, _, @, #
>	